{"type":"text","timestamp":1773436204804,"sessionID":"ses_316fcb4c5ffehqcHU7q5TvsiXt","part":{"id":"prt_ce908793e001r0dOTvOFeQVDMl","sessionID":"ses_316fcb4c5ffehqcHU7q5TvsiXt","messageID":"msg_ce9086ee0001NXsGWKPVMxvFMV","type":"text","text":"## Goal\n\nRetrofit all operational commands (`status`, `launch`, `cleanup`, `verify`, `merge`, `resume`, `retry`) with `--output json` support so they emit structured JSON output for agent consumption instead of human-readable text.\n\n## Instructions\n\n- Follow the pattern established in `src/lib/output.ts`: import `OutputFormat`, `resolveOutputFormat`, `output`, `outputError`, `outputMessage`\n- Each command needs an `outputFmt` option in its options interface and all output paths routed through the helpers\n- Reference pattern is `src/commands/tasks/archive.ts` and `src/commands/abort.ts`\n- Human-friendly text output must remain the default\n- JSON schemas should be consistent with tasks subcommand patterns\n- Use conventional commits with scope `json-operational-commands`\n- Commit after each logical unit of work\n- Do NOT push to remote or modify `undefined`\n- Run `bun run build` to verify when complete\n- Branch: `feature/json-operational-commands`, Base: `main`\n- Working directory: `/home/fulgidus/Documents/wt-wombo-json-operational-commands`\n\n## Discoveries\n\n- `status.ts` already had full JSON output support (outputFmt in options, buildStatusJson, uses `output()` helper) — it was listed in the task description but was already done\n- `launch.ts` already imported `outputError` and had `outputFmt` in `LaunchCommandOptions`, but only used it for the base branch validation error. Dry-run and no-features paths used raw `console.error`/`process.exit`\n- `abort.ts` is a good reference implementation — fully JSON-ified with `output()` for structured results\n- `index.ts` already passes `outputFmt` to `status`, `launch`, and `abort` commands, but NOT to `cleanup`, `verify`, `merge`, `retry`, or `resume`\n- TypeScript typecheck (`bun run typecheck`) passes after the completed changes\n- The output helpers: `output(fmt, data, textRenderer)` for structured data, `outputMessage(fmt, msg, extra)` for simple messages, `outputError(fmt, msg)` for errors (calls `process.exit`)\n\n## Accomplished\n\n### Completed (committed as `3be554e`):\n1. **cleanup.ts** — Full JSON support: dry-run emits structured JSON with session/worktree counts; actual cleanup emits result with `mux_sessions_killed`, `worktrees_removed`, `state_removed`, `logs_removed`, `remaining_branches`, `history_preserved`\n2. **verify.ts** — Full JSON support: no-wave/no-agents cases use `outputMessage`; results emit per-agent `build_passed`/`status`/`error` in structured JSON\n3. **merge.ts** — Full JSON support: dry-run, no-wave, no-agents, and result paths all use output helpers; result includes per-agent merge outcomes\n4. **retry.ts** — Full JSON support: all error paths use `outputError`; dry-run and result use `output()`; shows mode/pid/mux_session info\n5. **resume.ts** — Partial: imports added, options interface updated, error path uses `outputError`, triage `console.log` calls guarded with `if (fmt === \"text\")`, verification/merge phase logs guarded, no-agents-to-launch path uses `outputMessage`\n\n### In Progress (changes staged but NOT committed):\n6. **launch.ts** — Partially updated:\n   - Import updated to include `output`, `outputMessage` alongside existing `outputError`\n   - Dry-run path now emits structured JSON with selected features, schedule plan, config\n   - No-features error path now uses `outputError` instead of raw `console.error`/`process.exit`\n   - Still need to review: existing wave warning path, and other console output in the launch flow that should be guarded\n\n### Not Yet Done:\n7. **index.ts** — Needs to pass `outputFmt: args.outputFmt` to `cleanup`, `verify`, `merge`, `retry`, and `resume` command calls (currently missing from the switch cases)\n8. **Build verification** — Need to run `bun run build` after all changes\n\n## Relevant files / directories\n\n- **`src/lib/output.ts`** — Core output helpers (OutputFormat, output, outputError, outputMessage) — READ ONLY, not modified\n- **`src/commands/tasks/archive.ts`** — Reference pattern for JSON output — READ ONLY\n- **`src/commands/abort.ts`** — Another reference pattern (fully JSON-ified) — READ ONLY\n- **`src/commands/cleanup.ts`** — MODIFIED ✅ committed\n- **`src/commands/verify.ts`** — MODIFIED ✅ committed\n- **`src/commands/merge.ts`** — MODIFIED ✅ committed\n- **`src/commands/retry.ts`** — MODIFIED ✅ committed\n- **`src/commands/resume.ts`** — MODIFIED ✅ committed (triage/error paths), further changes may be needed for interactive resume text output\n- **`src/commands/launch.ts`** — MODIFIED 🔄 in progress (dry-run + no-features done, not yet committed)\n- **`src/commands/status.ts`** — READ ONLY, already had JSON support\n- **`src/index.ts`** — NEEDS MODIFICATION: must pass `outputFmt` to cleanup (line ~744), verify (~704), merge (~716), retry (~731), resume (~687)\n- **`AGENTS.md`** — READ for coding conventions\n- **`package.json`** — has `bun run build` and `bun run typecheck` scripts","time":{"start":1773436204802,"end":1773436204802}}}
