{"type":"text","timestamp":1773436251280,"sessionID":"ses_316fcb4c5ffehqcHU7q5TvsiXt","part":{"id":"prt_ce90989c6001PHNlnmiV9l8PaL","sessionID":"ses_316fcb4c5ffehqcHU7q5TvsiXt","messageID":"msg_ce90981ef001AcNllh9HRvcN42","type":"text","text":"Now I have a full understanding. Let me tackle everything systematically. The key insight is that `launch.ts` and `resume.ts` are **long-running orchestration commands** — they launch TUIs, monitoring loops, etc. The `--output json` support mostly matters for:\n1. **Error paths** (outputError) ✅ already done\n2. **Dry-run paths** (structured JSON result) ✅ already done for launch\n3. **Early exits / \"no agents found\"** (outputMessage) ✅ already done\n4. **Informational console.log** during active orchestration — these are runtime operational logs, not structured output. Guard them with `if (fmt === \"text\")` where it makes sense, but the monitoring loop output is inherently text-based TUI stuff.\n\nLet me now complete the remaining work:","time":{"start":1773436251280,"end":1773436251280}}}
